<p>&quot;Sure.&quot; The supervisor nodded his head. &quot;And we're the good guys.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This was some funny shit. I don't see why some people are wrinkling their noses at the concept, because it's obviously not promoting itself as canon - more as a jokey, unserious explanation for the immersion-wrecking little box at the top of every mainlister, and the way a fantastical and dangerous creature can appear in our html universe and then be wiped from existence in under 48 hours, because it was a giant telepathic Fifthist werewolf with red eyes and diamond claws that eats people (but only in multiples of five because Fifthism) and the Foundation thought it was really generic.</p>
<p>Normally we just ignore this stuff in-universe, because any explanation would unavoidably end up sounding really, really silly - but I'm glad someone went and tried to explain it anyway.</p>

							</div>

								
					
