			<div class="content" id="post-content-2838938">
									

<p>Awesome blend between comedy and serious &quot;realism&quot; in the mechanics of the rating system. The only source of confusion for me was the way a positive rating is determined. At the beginning of the info sheet, it refers to ratings being based off of the evaluations of observers. Does this mean stated, thought-out evaluations, or just the general reaction one feels? If the latter, how does the Ratings Committee exert complete influence over the ratings? In that case, every observer, not just the Ratings Committee members, would have an effect on the rating of an object. Also, I love how meta this is. Upvoted!</p>
<p>TL;DR - How an object's rating is determined based off of observers is a bit confusing (to me at least) and could be explained more effectively.</p>

